# Ghost-UI Root Environment Variables
# This file documents all required environment variables
# See individual packages for their specific .env.example files

# ===========================================
# Quick Reference
# ===========================================

# Backend (./backend/.env)
# - SUPABASE_URL              # Your Supabase project URL
# - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY # Service role key (for server-side operations)
# - OPENAI_API_KEY            # OpenAI API key for code fixer agent
# - GEMINI_API_KEY            # Google Gemini API key for accessibility analysis
# - N8N_WEBHOOK_URL           # (optional) n8n webhook URL for automation
# - DEBUG                     # Set to "true" for debug mode
# - BACKEND_PUBLIC_URL        # Public URL of the backend (for embed snippets)
# - ALLOWED_ORIGINS           # Additional CORS origins (comma-separated)

# Dashboard (./dashboard/.env)
# - VITE_BACKEND_URL          # Backend API URL
# - VITE_SUPABASE_URL         # Supabase project URL
# - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY    # Supabase anonymous key (for client-side auth)

# Extension (./extension/.env) - Paul's area
# - PLASMO_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL # Backend API URL for syncing preferences

# ===========================================
# Setup Instructions
# ===========================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the root directory
# 2. Copy ./backend/.env.example to ./backend/.env
# 3. Copy ./dashboard/.env.example to ./dashboard/.env
# 4. Copy ./extension/.env.example to ./extension/.env
# 5. Fill in all required values in each .env file
